      • canonicalName

        public String canonicalName()
        Returns the canonical name of this flavor - which is the name which should be used as an interface to users. The canonical name of this flavor is:
        • If it replaces one flavor, the canonical name of the flavor it replaces
        • If it replaces multiple or no flavors - itself
        The logic is that we can use this to capture the gritty details of configurations in exact flavor names but also encourage users to refer to them by a common name by letting such flavor variants declare that they replace the canonical name we want. However, if a node replaces multiple names, we have no basis for choosing one of them as the canonical, so we return the current as canonical.
